        "content": "<p>Issue <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/1047\">#1047</a></p>\n<p>Is this the required change for this issue:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">diff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">task</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">task</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2299bc7ac1f</span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"n\">fc305341cf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">100644</span>\n<span class=\"o\">---</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">task</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">task</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">101</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">101</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">deref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">Target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: Just an FFI call with no additional safety requirements.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">get_current</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"n\">TaskRef</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: If the current thread is still running, the current task is valid. Given</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">113</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">112</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">11</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">deref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">Target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returns the raw C pointer of the given task.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Task</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returns the group leader of the given task.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">group_leader</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Task</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: By the type invariant, we know that `self.0` is a valid task. Valid tasks always</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
